claim.claim-text:
1. A trunk comprising: 
a body 10 having a bottom 13 and a top 14, wherein a longitudinal depth of the bottom 13 is larger than that of the top 14; 
a cover unit 20 provided at one lateral side of the body; 
a first zipper 30 provided at the cover unit 20; 
a sector-like telescopic bag unit 40 connected between the body 10 and the cover unit 20; and 
a second zipper 50 installed between the body 10 and the cover unit 20; 
whereby a larger distance is formed by a pair of corner wheel 15 and a pair of leg 16 at the bottom 13 of the trunk so as to have a preferred stability; by the action of the first zipper 30 the cover unit 20 is capable of being opened or closed, by the action of the second zipper 50, the telescopic bag unit 40 is expanded outwards and closed inwards like a sector so as to increase the receiving volume of the trunk.

15. A trunk comprising a body 10, a cover unit 20, a first zipper 30, a telescopic bag unit 40, and a second zipper 50; wherein 
the body 10 is formed by a fiber cloth frame 11 and a framework 12; a longitudinal depth of a bottom 13 is large than that of the top 14; the bottom 13 is installed with a pair of corner wheels 15 and a pair of legs 16; the cover unit 20 is formed by a fiber cloth frame 21 and a cover 22; a lower cloth edge 21a of the fiber cloth frame 21 is seamed with the lower cloth edge 11a of the fiber cloth frame 11; a cloth edge 21b of the fiber cloth frame 21 is seamed to a cloth edge 22b of the cover 22; 
the first zipper 30 is formed between the fiber cloth frame 21 and the cover 22; a length of the first zipper 30 is equal or longer than that of the three edges of the fiber cloth frame 21 and the cover 22 for opening and closing the cover 22; 
the telescopic bag unit 40 is a fiber cloth frame having a non-uniform width; two lateral seaming edges are fixed to the fiber cloth frame 11 and the fiber cloth frame 21 for being connected to the body 10 and the cover unit 20; and 
the second zipper 50 is installed between the body 10 and the cover unit 20 with a configuration like an inverse U shape; a length of the second zipper 50 is equal or longer than that of the three lateral edges of the body 10 and the cover unit 20 so that the body 10 and the cover unit 20 are received tightly; the telescopic bag unit 40 is thus hidden therein; when the second zipper 50 is opened, the telescopic bag unit 40 is expanded outwards through a sector-like way so as to adjust the receiving space of the trunk; 
whereby a larger distance is formed by the corner wheel 15 and the leg 16 so as to have a preferred stability; even when the telescopic bag unit 40 is expanded outwards so as to increase the receiving volume for the trunk; the line of the gravitational center of the trunk passes through the center of the corner wheels 15 and legs 16 so as not to reduce the stability of the trunk thereby.

18. A trunk comprising a body 10, a cover unit 20, a first zipper 30, a telescopic bag unit 40, and a second zipper 50; wherein 
the body 10 is formed by a fiber cloth frame 11 and a framework 12; a longitudinal depth of a bottom 13 is larger than that of the top 14; the bottom 13 is installed with a pair of corner wheels 15 and a pair of legs 16; the body 10 further includes a pull rod 17, and a handle 18; 
the cover unit 20 is formed by a fiber cloth frame 21 and a cover 22; a cloth edge 21b of the fiber cloth frame 21 is seamed with the cloth edge 11b of the fiber cloth frame 11; 
the first zipper 30 has a length equal or longer than that of the three edges of the fiber cloth frame 21 and the cover 22 for opening and closing the cover 22; 
the telescopic bag unit 40 is of a fiber cloth frame having a non-uniform width; two lateral seaming edges are fixed to the fiber cloth frame 21 and the cover 22; and 
the second zipper 50 is installed between the fiber cloth frame 21 and the cover 22 with a configuration like an inverse U shape; a length of the second zipper 50 is equal or longer than that of the three lateral edges of the fiber cloth frame 21 and the cover 22 so that fiber cloth frame 21 and the cover 22 are received tightly; the telescopic bag unit 40 is thus hidden; when the second zipper 50 is opened, the telescopic bag unit 40 is expanded outwards using a sector-like way so as to adjust the receiving space of the trunk; 
whereby a larger distance is formed by a pair of corner wheel 15 and a pair of leg 16 so as to have a preferred stability; the structure is very simple and steady; when the telescopic bag unit 40 is expanded outwards the receiving volume of the trunk is increased, and the line of the gravitational center of the trunk substantial passes through the center of the corner wheels 15 and legs 16 so as not to reduce the stability of the trunk.
